name: internal combustion engine production, passenger car | internal combustion engine, passenger car | Cutoff, U
description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/6442/documentation

This dataset describes the production of an internal combustion engine (ICE) for a passenger car. The entries are given per kg engine. The original data has been derived for an ICE of approximately 275kg. The information described in this dataset has been obtained starting from the "Life Cycle Inventory of the Golf A4" made by Schweimer and Levin.  The final dataset has been published in Althaus and Gauch: "Vergleichende Oekobilanz der Elektromobilität: Elektromobilität bersus konventionelle Mobilität mit Bio- und fossilen Treibstoffen".

The dataset takes as input the raw materials and the energy inputs required for the production process and includes the production facility.

The dataset returns the finished internal combustion engine as well as the output scrap fractions from the production process.
category: C:Manufacturing/29:Manufacture of motor vehicles, trailers and semi-trailers/291:Manufacture of motor vehicles/2910:Manufacture of motor vehicles

processDocumentation.technologyDescription: The dataset is based on current car technologies.
processDocumentation.dataTreatmentDescription: The original data has been taken from literature (Schweimer and Levine, "Life Cycle Inventory of the Golf A4", 2000).
